	<Title>
		Avoid razor burn
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the best way to shave: 1. Press a warm wash cloth on your skin before shaving to soften the hair. Or shave after a warm bath or shower. 2. Apply shaving cream, lotion or gel before shaving to protect and lubricate your skin. 3. Use a clean, sharp razor. 4. Shave in the direction of hair growth, not against it. 5. Rinse your skin with warm water.&lt;/p&gt;
